73
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:14,930
I heard he turned down your offer.

74
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,950
So, that's Zang Hai?

75
00:06:19,950 --> 00:06:23,160
He described himself as a man pursuing fame and fortune.

76
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:26,950
Because of who he is, he refused the owner of Zhen Tower.

77
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:28,720
He seems to have some principles after all.

78
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,760
What's going on again?

79
00:06:32,070 --> 00:06:33,830
Can't you tell, Eighth Young Master?

80
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,680
He's determined to stake everything on the Marquis of Pingjin

81
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:39,380
to prove to the world that he's not an ordinary man.

82
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:41,630
He can achieve greatness

83
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:43,590
but it's a pity.

84
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,950
He violated your taboos.

85
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:49,220
With the Marquis' temperament,

86
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:51,290
if he ever regains military command,

87
00:06:51,290 --> 00:06:54,140
he'll lead an expedition to the border to display his power.

88
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:56,160
Yang Zhen was a petty man.

89
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,780
He wasn't a threat at all

90
00:06:57,780 --> 00:06:59,680
but Zang Hai is different.

91
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:04,140
I don't want to see a talent like him under the Marquis' command.

92
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:06,140
You want to get rid of him?

93
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:10,830
"Good fortune doesn't last forever. Flowers don't bloom all year round."

94
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:13,270
He's now the Chief Aide of the Marquis of Pingjin

95
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:16,160
but with all the matters coming his way,

96
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:21,360
he'll be careless in his work and lose the favor of the Marquis.

97
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:26,700
Steward.

98
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,490
Sir Zang, you're back.

99
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:31,550
These are...

100
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:33,630
These are gifts from outsiders.

101
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,950
They're for you.

102
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:39,530
Now that you're favored by the Marquis,

103
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:43,410
everyone's rushing to curry favor with you.

104
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:48,000
Look. A jade belt hook carved with dragons and clouds.

105
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,120
Look at the material used.

106
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:52,050
It's top quality.

107
00:07:52,050 --> 00:07:53,630
Come and look at this, too.

108
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:55,100
Come, unroll it.

109
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:59,490
"Peacocks and a Loquat Tree" by Cui Zixi of the Song Dynasty.

110
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:02,240
One glance, and you know it's genuine.

111
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,560
Look at this. 
    

112
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,950
These leaves and feathers

113
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:08,600
are rich, vibrant, and detached from worldly feelings. 
    

114
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,900
Absolutely elegant.

115
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:15,890
Steward, why are these accompanying notes without names?

116
00:08:17,610 --> 00:08:19,070
You...

117
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,100
Take them all inside.

118
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:28,510
Sir, you must not know.

119
00:08:28,510 --> 00:08:30,380
These are reciprocal gifts.

120
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:33,480
It's an unwritten rule in the capital.

121
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,120
Even if you want to return them, you won't know who to return them to.

122
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,890
When they need my help,

123
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:42,490
they'll show up and identify their gifts.

124
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:45,910
Sir, you're smart.

125
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:47,320
Does the Marquis know?

126
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:51,250
These gifts are in the Marquis Residence. Of course, he knows.

127
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:53,240
Did he say anything?

128
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,510
He doesn't bother with these things.

129
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,910
Since the gifts are meant for you,

130
00:08:57,910 --> 00:09:01,750
you can handle them as you see fit.

131
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,440
I see.

132
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:06,120
I'll accept these gifts then.

133
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,790
Did he accept the items?

134
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,390
He did.

135
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:13,750
Did you explain the meaning of a reciprocal gift?

136
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,120
I did.

137
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:18,550
He also knows that once the gifts are accepted,

138
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:21,470
he needs to eliminate disasters and solve problems for them.

139
